What does this mean...
/$ cd /var/www/claudebeat && sudo git pull
fatal: detected dubious ownership in repository at '/var/www/claudebeat'
To add an exception for this directory, call:

	git config --global --add safe.directory /var/www/claudebeat


● Git is running as root (via sudo) but the directory is owned by www-data — a security check added in Git 2.35. Just
  run the fix it suggests, then pull:

  sudo git config --global --add safe.directory /var/www/claudebeat
  sudo git pull

  That's a one-time fix. Future pulls in that directory will work without the error.



